Nordson Corporation Announces Promotion of Gregory A. Thaxton to Corporate Senior Vice President | Business Wire
























































Nordson Corporation Announces Promotion of Gregory A. Thaxton to 
      Corporate Senior Vice President






December 02, 2011 04:00 PM Eastern Standard Time



WESTLAKE, Ohio--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Nordson 
      Corporation (NASDAQ: NDSN) today announced the promotion of Gregory 
      A. Thaxton as a Corporate Senior Vice President of the company. Thaxton, 
      previously elected as a Nordson Corporate Vice President in 2007, serves 
      as Nordson’s Vice President, Chief Financial Officer reporting directly 
      to Nordson President and CEO Michael F. Hilton.
    


      “Greg is well deserving of this promotion to Corporate Senior Vice 
      President,” said Hilton. “Nordson has significantly improved its 
      financial performance during Greg’s time as Chief Financial Officer, and 
      his sound judgment continues to be invaluable in setting our strategic 
      direction moving forward. He is an outstanding partner to our business 
      units, an excellent mentor to many, and a steward of our corporate 
      values.”
    

      As Nordson’s Chief Financial Officer, Thaxton directs the corporate 
      accounting and reporting, internal audit, tax, treasury, investor 
      relations and business control functions. He became a part of the 
      executive leadership team in February 2006 when he was named Corporate 
      Controller and Chief Accounting officer. Previously, Thaxton served as 
      Group Controller for the Pacific South Division and the Finishing and 
      Coating Systems segment, as well as the Automotive Systems and UV Curing 
      Systems businesses. Thaxton joined Nordson in 1989.
    

      Thaxton, a certified public accountant, holds a bachelor's degree in 
      accounting from Miami University and a master's degree in business 
      administration from Baldwin-Wallace College. He is a board member of 
      Lorain County Community College Foundation and Nordson Corporation 
      Foundation. In addition, he is a member of the American Institute of 
      Certified Public Accountants (AICPA), the Ohio Society of Certified 
      Public Accountants, the MAPI CFO Council, and the National Investor 
      Relations Institute (NIRI).
    

      In addition to Thaxton, Nordson’s executive officer team includes 
      Michael F. Hilton, President and Chief Executive Officer; John J. Keane, 
      Senior Vice President, Advanced Technology Systems; Peter G. Lambert, 
      Senior Vice President, Adhesive Dispensing Systems; Douglas C. 
      Bloomfield, Vice President, Industrial Coating Systems; Gregory P. Merk, 
      Vice President, Pacific South Division; Shelly M. Peet, Vice President; 
      Robert E. Veillette, Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary; and 
      James E. DeVries, Vice President of Global Continuous Improvement.
    

      Nordson Corporation delivers precision technology solutions that help 
      customers increase speed, productivity and up-time, enable new products 
      and features, and decrease material usage. The company engineers, 
      manufactures and markets differentiated products and systems used for dispensing
adhesives, 
      coatings, 
      sealants, biomaterials 
      and other materials, fluid 
      management, testing 
      and inspection, and UV 
      curing and surface 
      plasma treatment, all supported by application expertise and direct 
      global sales and service. Nordson serves a wide variety of consumer 
      non-durable, durable and technology end markets including packaging, 
      nonwovens, electronics, medical, appliances, energy, transportation, 
      building and construction, and general product assembly and finishing. 
      Founded in 1954 and headquartered in Westlake, Ohio, the company has 
      operations and support offices in more than 30 countries. Visit Nordson 
      at www.nordson.com, 
      twitter.com/Nordson_Corp, 
      or Facebook.com/Nordson.
    


Contacts

      Nordson CorporationJames R. Jaye, 440-414-5639Director, 
      Communications & Investor RelationsJim.Jaye@nordson.com














